In this article, President Barack Obama proclaims November 2013 as Military Family Month. He acknowledges the sacrifices and contributions made by military families and emphasizes the importance of supporting them. The article highlights the efforts of the Joining Forces initiative, led by First Lady Michelle Obama and Dr. Jill Biden, to engage citizens and businesses in supporting military families. It also mentions actions taken to improve mental health care and extend benefits to legally married same-sex couples. The President calls on all Americans to honor military families through private actions and public service.